a bag as you fill the bucket. The directions suggest using somewhere between 1 and 5 gallons of water. I used 5 gallons.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-6395 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/07\/Steep-your-manure-tea-for-several-days-for-a-more-potent-fertilizer.jpg\" alt=\"Steep your manure tea for several days for a more potent fertilizer\" width=\"735\" height=\"490\" data-pin-description=\"Did you know succulents need fertilizer? Find out how to fertilize your succulents in this post! Choosing a fertilizer specifically for succulents is extremely important. This post covers the best options for succulent fertilizer. #fertilizer #fertilizingsucculents #succulentfertilizer #succulents #succulent #succulentcare #indoorsucculents #outdoorsucculent #succulenttips #fertilizerhelp #howtouseteafertilizer #healthysucculentgarden #fertilizertips #succulentgarden #fertilizerforgarden\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/07\/Steep-your-manure-tea-for-several-days-for-a-more-potent-fertilizer-500x333.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/07\/Steep-your-manure-tea-for-several-days-for-a-more-potent-fertilizer-700x467.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/07\/Steep-your-manure-tea-for-several-days-for-a-more-potent-fertilizer.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Cover the bucket and let the tea bag sit in the water for a few days. I didn't want to fish the bag out of the water later, so I left the string hanging over the edge of the bucket.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-6389 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/07\/Cover-the-manure-tea-while-it-steeps.jpg\" alt=\"Cover the manure tea while it steeps\" width=\"735\" height=\"490\" data-pin-description=\"Did you know succulents need fertilizer? Find out how to 